---- MODULE HDiskSynod ----
plus
MODULE ZSequencesModule -- Defines operators on finite zero-indexed sequences where length n of sequence S represented as function whose domain 0..(n -1) is set {0,...,n−1}.
LOCAL INSTANCE FiniteSet, Naturals SET_OF NaturalNumbers.
CONSTANTS EmptyZSeq = <<>> -- The empty zero-indexed sequences are defined to be an empty sequence (<<>>). 
VARIABLE ZIndices(s) AS SetOfNaturalNumbers DEFINED BY s IN {0..Cardinality(DOMAIN s)-1}.  
-- Variable for storing the indices of a zero-indexed sequences. The domain is set by Cardinality (number of elements in sequence). 
SPECIFICATION Spec -- Defines operators on finite sets, where length n represents an element S represented as function whose domain {0..(n -1)}.  
INVARIANTS TypeInvariant;   
-- Invariants are defined to ensure the type invariant. The only way for a sequence s of lengh 2 can be reached is by appending two elements at end, so we define it here as an empty set (<<>>).    
LOCAL INSTANCE Sequences SET_OF ZSeqOfLength;   -- Defines all zero-indexed sequences with length n.   
VARIABLE a PRECEED b AS SetDefinedBy(ZIndices, Naturals) DEFINITION BY RECURSION ONLY IF (a ≡b).    
-- Variable for lexicographic order on sets of zero-indexed sequences with length n. The domain is set by ZIndices and the definition recursively checks if a < b or not, based upon indices in sequence s(i+1) to i<n (lengths are checked from 0).
-- Defines all rotations for each element of zero-indexed sequences with length n. The domain is set by ZIndices and the definition recursively shifts elements at index r one position left, based upon indices in sequence s(i+1) to i<n (lengths are checked from 0).
-- Defines all rotations for each element of zero-indexed sequences with length n. The domain is set by ZIndices and the definition recursively shifts elements at index r one position left, based upon indices in sequence s(i+1) to i<n (lengths are checked from 0).
-- Defines all rotations for each element of zero-indexed sequences with length n. The domain is set by ZIndices and the definition recursively shifts elements at index r one position left, based upon indices in sequence s(i+1) to i<n (lengths are checked from 0).
-- Defines all rotations for each element of zero-indexed sequences with length n. The domain is set by ZIndices and the definition recursively shifts elements at index r one position left, based upon indices in sequence s(i+1) to i<n (lengths are checked from 0).
